entries.femaleVariant: Can't they just have us take 'em out, one by one?
He used to work for Militech. I'd see him, but you couldn't talk to the guy, he'd never answer.
Sooo… are those two dead or what?
So there's this Blackwall, right? And we're on one side, and crazy ass AIs are on the other.
They know some of the big Voodoo names. We know 'em – Aveg, Placide…
But they're after the BBS, data forts.
Why's that gotta stop us from beatin' their big dogs to a bloody pulp.
Fuck, man, it's just a job. You got a personal beef or somethin'?
No. Just want the worms to crawl back where they came from.
Where, Haiti? That rock's been abandoned fifty years.
So he got promoted and what? He recognize you now?
Oh yeah. Looked at me like he just stepped in a pile o' dog shit.
Nah, only froze 'em with Aardvark for now.
Wait, isn't that black soft?
Yeah, choom – but these fuckers don't hold back.
Shiiit... Aardvark? Get caught with that and you're doin' ten.
Not to mention the "personality realignment."
Only if you ain't battin' for their team. Their agents get to take the gloves off in humanity's service.
'Fore that, there was just one big, open Net. Stretched everywhere.
But then this dude, Rache Bartmoss, I think his name was...
Six days on Watch duty, and everyone's a fucking Net expert... Jesus.
